Justin Tyopuusu, Jalingo The General Officer Commanding 3 Division of the Nigerian Army, Jos, Maj. Gen.  Nuhu Angbazo, on Wednesday said the army had commenced operation in Taraba State to fish out those behind the Jukun/Tiv crisis. Angbazo said this in Takum while addressing religious and traditional leaders, women and youth groups on the need for peaceful coexistence in the area. The GOC, who was represented by Brig. Gen. Briggs Daniel, said the Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Tukur Buratai, had authorised the Operation Ayem Apatuma  in the area to flush out bad eggs. Angbazo solicited support and cooperation of the people to enable the security operatives to restore peace back to the area, adding that their duty was to bring peace back to the area. He expressed sadness that most of the schools in the area were closed because of the unrest thereby depriving children the right to education. The GOC urged religious and traditional leaders to preach the gospel of peace to their followers in the interest of unity and development. On his part, the Brigade Commander, 23 Brigade, Yola, Brig. Gen. S.G. Mohammed, called on those in possession of firearms to surrender them to the police or face the wrath of the law. He advised leaders at all levels to embrace peace even as he solicited for vital information from members of the public to enable them to succeed in their bid to restore peace to the state. In his remarks, the Caretaker Committee Chairman of Takum Local Government, Shiban Tikari, implored the Tiv and Jukun people to tolerate and live in peace with one another. He added that they should stop peddling wrong information, which he said, was not helping situation. Copyright PUNCH.
